$(DDOX_UNITTEST_FOOTER __unittest_L1372_C1)

 Lexical analyzer that converts source code into tokens.

 The lexer reads through QScript source code character by character,
 identifying and producing tokens according to the QScript grammar.
 It handles comments, whitespace, and provides error reporting with
 line and column information.
Example:
Test basic tokenization of simple tokens.$(DDOX_UNITTEST_HEADER __unittest_L491_C1)
---
auto lexer = new Lexer("( ) { } ; ,");
assert(lexer.tokenize(), "Should tokenize successfully");
assert(lexer.tokens.length == 7, "Should have 6 tokens plus EOF");
assert(lexer.tokens[0].type == TokenType.LPAREN, "First token should be LPAREN");
assert(lexer.tokens[1].type == TokenType.RPAREN, "Second token should be RPAREN");

